section.section:
Buses and trucks 80 inches or more in overall width shall have:
On the front, two clearance lamps, one at each side, and on those manufactured or assembled after June 1, 1971, three identification lamps meeting the specifications of subsection (c) of this section;
On the rear, two clearance lamps, one at each side, and after June 1, 1970, three identification lamps meeting the specifications of subsection (c) of this section;
On each side, two side marker lamps, one at or near the front and one at or near the rear; and
On each side, two reflectors, one at or near the front and one at or near the rear.

Trailers and semitrailers 80 inches or more in overall width shall have:
On the front, two clearance lamps, one at each side;
On the rear, two clearance lamps, one at each side, and after June 1, 1971, three identification lamps meeting the specifications of subsection (c) of this section;
On each side, two side marker lamps, one at or near the front and one at or near the rear; and
On each side, two reflectors, one at or near the front and one at or near the rear.
